{
  "texts": [
    "Digitization of healthcare has enabled Artificial Intelligence (AI) methods to integrate big data for effective patient management [1].",
    "AI models particularly deep learning algorithms such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), vision transformers, and Large Language Models (LLMs) require large amounts of training data to achieve acceptable performances [2][3][4][5].",
    "This has increased the demand for digital data in all domains of healthcare, including dentistry [6].",
    "Healthcare data available for training AI models includes Electronic Health Records (EHRs), radiographs, clinical photographs, etc [1].",
    "This extensive patient data can be curated to form large-scale datasets for training AI on healthcare-related problems.However, some pertinent concerns prevail with AI models trained on these \"traditionally acquired\" datasets."
  ]
}